column5: Hey guys,  We have been out in full filght on the Bay of Quinte the past little while, with great success! We are averaging 20-25 fish per day with lots of Walleye being caught in the 7-12 lb range! We have been able to locate some amazing fish who seem to be co-operating quite well! Multiple clients (as well as myself) have smashed our personal best fish!  Here are some pics from the past two weekends.  My new personal best... 10.5 lbs!     A client with a beauty 7lb'er   Grant from G2 with a MONSTER 11lb'er            For more pictures and info feel free to visit the G2 Angling Website
Nice add  Some nice fish there!  S.
Couple new pictures added at the bottom!
Love that last shot, black and white, with Walleye Gold...fantastic!!!!!!!!!!!!
Can't beat a day like that!!!  Congrats on your PB Stoty & to all involved Thanks for sharing Leechman
Some nice fish there Jamie!!  Now 25 fish a day.. how many clients and G2's does it take to get that many.. ie how many fish each are you catching a day?
That pic of the walleye be pointed like a gun looks familiar, think ive seen it done before with steelhead
Holy frig thats a huge walleye! Congrats on your PB.
Sorry for the mix up in the past. Great job out there man! You really caught a huge walleye man, congrads!  Mike
